pageTitle: Renovating hay and pasture fields | TheSpringfieldSun.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {32076=Copyright © 2015, 18756=If you have a less-than-productive grass pasture or hayfield, following a few simple renovation techniques could increase the field’s productivity. Some things you can do include planting a legume such as red clover, controlling pests and adding lime and fertilizer. Be aware though, some techniques require you to start as early as the middle of February. Adding legumes to pasture and hayfields has several benefits including higher yields, improved quality, nitrogen fixation and more summer growth.}
